  01010011    	  10111001
+01100110   	+01110100
—------------     —------------
  10111001     00101110

final answer: 00101110

The checksum is used 

The receiver detects errors by adding the checksums to the 1’s complement. This should result in all 1’s. Therefore, any detected 0’s are known to be errors. This mathematical property of one’s complement makes it beneficial to use for error detection vs the plain sum.


